<!-- Localization documentation-->
<!--Localisation in android for the India region-> Right click on res -> select New->
Android Resource Directory -> In available qualifiers select locale -> Choose language
and specific region. You can check the preview of the text in the layout preview, selecting
another locale using dropsdown-->

<!-- You can put the localization for the images also, we need to create the different folders
for different regions. Create folder in resource with right click on the res package and select
New ▸ Android resource directory-> create a new drawable folder for the en-GB locale.
en:English as the language and GB:United Kingdom as the region. save all the images with same name-->

<!-- There is also RTL right to left that has to be checked for the languages which are written
from right to left. To test for this:  confirm the app has enabled RTL support by checking in
AndroidManifest.xml that application contains android:supportsRtl=”true”. In the layout file select
preview right to left. On real device, enable developer options. In the code for the debug builds:
debug {
  pseudoLocalesEnabled true
}
Find the pseudolocales in the Languages section of Settings. And select Arabic-->
